<div class="welcome">
  <header id="site-header" class="site-header">
    <%= render partial: "shared/site_header", locals: {classes: "2x"} %>

    <div class="container">

      <div class="header-description">
        <h2>Increase productivity across your organization by 10%</h2>
        <<hr/>
        <h3>Employees receive a daily reminder of which emails they've forgotten to reply to.</h3>
        <h3>Managers receive real-time email analytics .</h3>
        <%# link_to "Start my Free Trial", omniauth_authorize_path("user", "google_oauth2"),
                    class: "btn btn-lg btn-header" %>

        <form action="" method="POST" class="reserve1">
          <script
          src="https://checkout.stripe.com/checkout.js" class="stripe-button"
          data-key="pk_test_dVDRjuxnmFU9tLH1UjDt7Jhx"
          data-name="Productive.email"
          data-description="Productive.email Deposit ($500.00)"
          data-image="/assets/productive_email_logo.png"
          data-panelLabel="Reserve"
          data-label="Reserve Your Instance"
          data-allowRememberMe="false"
          data-class="xxxxx"
          >
          </script>
        </form>

      </div>

      <div class="header-features">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6 header-feature">
            <h3><%= fa_icon "group" %>&nbsp;EMPLOYEES, You're forgetting someone</h3>

            <p>
              Your inbox fills up fast. Your boss needs you to follow up with a customer,
              accounting needs the monthly revenue numbers, your co-workers are bugging you
              to go out to lunch. Along with personal emails, you've got daily deals from Groupon
              and some guy sending you daily fitness tips.
            </p>

            <p>
              Who do you need to follow up with? Which customer is slipping through the cracks?
            </p>

          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-6 header-feature">
            <h3><%= fa_icon "random" %>&nbsp;Follow up. Follow through.</h3>

            <p>
              Maybe you sent an email to your programmer three days ago and haven't gotten a response?
              Productive.email will remind you. Yesterday your customer asked for a refund while you were cooking
              dinner.
              Don't worry, we'll remind you. Your boss just sent a ten paragraph email outlining a number
              of key questions for an important initiative.
              Productive.email will call out those key questions for you.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6 header-feature">
            <h3>Relax. You don't have do anything. That's our job.</h3>

            <p>
              Productive.email analyzes your email and with the help of some advanced algorithms,
              figures out exactly which of your emails deserve a response. No cumbersome settings of reminders,
              flagging messages or labeling.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-6 header-feature">
            <h3>You don't have to remember anything.</h3>
            <p>
              Everyday you'll receive a simple, daily email summarizing who's waiting to hear from you and who
              hasn't responded to you. No nagging reminders or popups messages.
              Just a simple list of email to respond to.
              You're never going to forget to follow up ever again.
              Your customers are going to be so impressed (as if they weren't already).
            </p>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- /.header-features -->

    </div>
    <!-- /.container -->
  </header>

  <section id="slider" class="slider text-center">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">

          <div id="slider-carousel" class="carousel slide">
            <div class="carousel-inner">
              <div class="item active">
                <%= image_tag "emails.jpg" %>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <%= image_tag "question_highlights.jpg" %>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a class="carousel-control lef" href="#slider-carousel" data-slide="prev">&lsaquo;</a>
